# React Compiler

This project uses React Compiler, which automatically memoizes components and hooks.

## Do NOT use

- `useCallback` — the compiler handles function identity
- `useMemo` — the compiler handles computed values
- `React.memo` — the compiler handles component memoization

## Use instead

- Plain functions and inline values
- Let the compiler optimize re-renders

```tsx
// ❌ Avoid
const handleClick = useCallback(() => doSomething(), []);
const value = useMemo(() => computeExpensive(a, b), [a, b]);
export default React.memo(MyComponent);

// ✅ Prefer
function handleClick() {
  doSomething();
}
const value = computeExpensive(a, b);
export default function MyComponent() { ... }
```
